# Story Conventions

- Colocate `<name>.stories.tsx` inside the component's folder: `src/components/ui/<name>/<name>.stories.tsx`.
- Import the component (and any other UI components) via the alias `@/components/ui/<name>`, not relative `./` paths.
- Import types from `@storybook/react-vite` (not `@storybook/react`):

```tsx
import type { Meta, StoryObj } from '@storybook/react-vite'
import { Button } from '@/components/ui/button'

const meta = {
  title: 'UI/Button',
  component: Button,
  tags: ['autodocs'],
} satisfies Meta<typeof Button>

export default meta
type Story = StoryObj<typeof meta>

export const Default: Story = {}
```

- Use `title: 'UI/<ComponentName>'` so everything groups under the UI section.
- Always add `tags: ['autodocs']` and use `satisfies Meta<typeof X>`.
- Provide a `Default` story plus variant/state stories; expose key props through `argTypes` controls.
- Components with required props must set them in `meta.args` (e.g. Accordion needs `args: { type: 'single', collapsible: true }`).
